Class EFlowSM

Direct Known Subclasses:
EFlow1SM
public class EFlowSM
extends LineSM

Electron flow arrow drawing mode. This class is under development, use it at your own risk!

Specification (by Robert B. Grossman). A user clicks and holds on an atom or a bond to begin drawing an arrow, drags to an atom, bond, or incipient bond, and releases to complete the arrow. Rules:

  • If the electron source is an atom A, then the electron sink must be any other atom B (electron transfer only) or an A-X bond or incipient bond.
  • If the electron source is a bond A-B, then the electron sink must be A, B, or an A-X or B-X bond or incipient bond.
Note: This class is the successor of Saravana Kannan's EFlowSO.
